    Scope and Contents
WWII CONSCIENTIOUS OBJECTORS PROJECT 
Jack, a Unitarian Minister, discusses the use of non-violent means to bring about social change. He recalls WWII conscientious objectors from Union Seminary and discusses pacifism, the peace movement, non-violent demonstrations, race relations in Chicago following WWII, racial equality, his work in Africa, the World Conference on Religion and World Peace, socialism and the Vietnam War. 2 tapes, 180 mins., 38 pp. 
Interview by C. Arthur Bradley, 1988 
